  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "English Teacher",
  "description": "<p><strong>Roles & Responsibilities</strong></p><p>We are looking for a highly passionate and responsible language teacher to join our language school. The successful candidate shall be tasked to conduct English teaching, as well as establish relationships with our students to inspire loyalty and learning progress.</p><ul><li>40 hour work-week, with 2 off days a week (1 week-day and 1 weekend), (Subject to rostering).</li><li>Small class size: 1 to 1~5.</li><li>Teaching materials provided.</li><li><strong>Bonus structure even for teachers!</strong></li></ul><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Research and develop academic framework and prepare teaching syllabus to meet the needs of our students. Preparing and delivering lessons and tutorial classes according to the course syllabus.</li><li>Conducting private or group classes in an engaging and relevant manner.</li><li>Providing academic support to students, participating in orientation and marketing events.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Native English speaker.</li><li>Experience in teaching English and other academic courses to mainland Chinese students.</li><li>Bachelor’s degree (preferably major in Education or Languages).</li><li>Excellent interpersonal, communication, presentation and organisational skills</li><li>Highly motivated, good working attitude and strong sense of responsibility.</li><li>At least 3 years of experience in teaching language courses.</li><li>Experience in teaching in a multilingual environment and academic assessment.</li></ul><p>We offer an attractive package with excellent employee benefits, conducive working environment and career growth potential. Remuneration and benefits will commensurate with qualifications and experience.</p><p>Interested candidates are invited to apply online stating your current and expected salary and date of availability.</p>",
